    <h1>Monte Carlo Methods</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">MIT OCW 18.S096 + 15.450 (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Monte Carlo methods price derivatives by simulating thousands of random paths for the underlying asset, then averaging the discounted payoffs. The law of large numbers guarantees convergence; variance reduction makes it practical.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: simulated price paths fanning out from a single point -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 200" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
